Food quality is really good! Not overly greasy. Good vegetarian options and if you order over $20 you get two free sodas. Easy to order and the person on the phone was very pleasant.  Edit: (5/4/18) I’ve been seeing some reviews saying that the quality of the food has lessened. I ordered the chicken chow fun and this time it didn’t have as many noodles/was a bit more greasy than usual. The dumplings and faux chicken were good as always, though.

The quality used to be better.  The last two times over the past month has shown a big decline in quality.  The General Tzo's shrimp had an under cooked thick paste-like breading around each shrimp.  The Pu-Pu platter had a satay beef on a stick that was all gristle and chewy.  A prior time we ordered sesame shrimp and it was just breaded shrimp without any kind of flavoring or sauce. the egg rolls are filled with tough cabbage.   A big disappointment - perhaps they have changed their chef.

Delicious tasting Chinese food at affordable pricing. A chicken and broccoli with chicken fried rice and a pork roll for lunch special was $6.25 (.15c more if you want a shrimp roll instead). The service was fast and attentive but my only qualm is that same person taking the money/orders is the same person who does meal prep (and doesn't wash their hands in between each task). They are also a cash only establishment.
